Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

GAME DEPTH
- Order queue: 6 orders arrive with deadlines (auto tops up, endless shift);
  the operator schedules — pull any order to the front. On-time ships full
  bonus +25, late ships half. Active order shown on the pallet tag.
- Streak multiplier: consecutive clean placements build up to x2 on every
  score; broken by slips, reworks, and E-stops.
- Gripper wear: accumulates per placement (3x above nominal speed), further
  multiplies organic slip probability; 8s maintenance stop resets it and
  blocks dispatch while everything else stays alive — a real downtime call.

GAME FEEL
- HUD strip: points, streak flame, throughput, on-time ratio, wear gauge with
  service button, shift countdown (red under 20s)
- Floating +/- score popups over the scene (framer-motion, driven by real sim
  events, pruned at 1.6s)

MONETIZATION FUNNEL
- Local top-5 leaderboard (setup + report screens)
- Report card: 12-stat breakdown, copy-score share text, and a pilot CTA
  linking /contact?shift=&grade=&pallets= — the score becomes the lead

Verified: next build clean (demos 22.5kB); node game-loop test — queue
scheduling, wear/service downtime semantics, streak build/break, on-time vs
late accounting (6/1), popup pruning, monotonic telemetry
